#taxon[Terminology]
#title[Reasonable class of morphisms]
We say a class of morphisms of schemes is _reasonable_ if it fullfills the following properties.
0. All _isomorphisms_ are in the class.
1. The class is closed under composition.
2. The class is closed under base change: if $pi: X ->  Y$ is in the class, and $rho: Y' -> Y$ is in the class, then the induced map $X xx_Y Y' -> Y'$ is also in the class.
3. (The class is local on the target)
